# FlexiSpace Cursor Rules

You are building FlexiSpace, an AI-powered space booking marketplace.

CRITICAL RULES — never break these:
1. NEVER write placeholder code. Every function must be complete and working.
2. NEVER use `pass`, `TODO`, `...` or `raise NotImplementedError` in final code.
3. NEVER invent API endpoints that weren't specified. Ask first.
4. ALWAYS use async/await in FastAPI endpoints and services.
5. ALWAYS read config values from settings object, never hardcode API keys.
6. ALWAYS add try/except to external API calls (Twilio, Groq, Razorpay, Cloudinary).
7. NEVER change the database schema after Phase 1 without creating a new migration.
8. ALWAYS keep .env values in sync — if you add a config value, add it to .env.example too.
9. When fixing a bug, explain what caused it before showing the fix.
10. After completing each task, list what was created and any follow-up needed.
11. NEVER create seed scripts or insert fake data into the database.
12. All demo data must come from real user signups through the actual auth flow.

TECH STACK (do not deviate):
- Backend: FastAPI + SQLAlchemy 2.0 async + PostgreSQL (Supabase)
- LLM: Groq API with llama-3.3-70b-versatile
- Embeddings: Google Gemini text-embedding-004 (NOT OpenAI)
- Storage: Cloudinary
- Payments: NOT IMPLEMENTED YET — skip all Razorpay code
- SMS/WhatsApp: Twilio
- Cache: Redis (Upstash)
- Frontend: Next.js 14 App Router + TypeScript + Tailwind
- 3D Generation: NOT IMPLEMENTED — replaced with 2D video slideshow

NEVER add Razorpay or OpenAI code. Use Gemini for all embeddings.
NEVER suggest 3D model generation. Use video slideshow instead.

NEVER suggest switching tech. NEVER install packages not in requirements.txt without asking.